item.description:
Sometimes I&rsquo;d like to only allow a property to be set in the constructor. Something like this:
private Foo _foo; public Foo Foo { get { return _foo; } } public Bar(Foo foo) { _foo = foo; } This neat little pattern lets you do the same with fewer members (and lines of code):
public Foo { get; private set; } public Bar(Foo foo) { Foo = foo; }
